r /><br />Oh, never mind. I also have COMPILE_TEST on, so it ends up disabling<br />GCOV_PROFILE_ALL and UBSAN_SANITIZE_ALL.<br /><br />And yeah, this seems to be a gcc bug. It generates a ton of stack<br />slots for temporaries. It's -fsanitize=object-size that seems to do<br />it.<br /><br />And "-fstack-reuse=all" doesn't seem to make any difference.<br /><br />So I think<br /><br /> (a) our stack size check is good to catch this<br /><br /> (b) gcc and -fsanitize=object-size is basically an unusable combination<br /><br />and it's not a bug in the kernel.<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
